---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Dave Sharp Auction">
  <header class="bar">
    <a class="bar-mark" href="/">
      Dave Sharp
      <span>Live Auction</span>
    </a>
    <a class="bar-back" href="/">&larr; Back to the auction</a>
  </header>

  <main class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="updated">Last updated &mdash; May 2026</div>

    <p>
      This auction site (<strong>auction.davesharp.art</strong>) is run by Dave Sharp
      (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;us&rdquo;). This policy explains what personal
      information we collect when you register and bid, how we use it, and the
      rights you have over it.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>When you register to bid</strong> — your name, your email address,
      and your phone number if you choose to give it (it is optional).
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Email verification</strong> — we email you a one-time code to confirm
      the email address is yours.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Your bids</strong> — every bid you place is recorded against you, with
      its amount and the time it was placed.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>A sign-in cookie</strong> — once your email is verified we set a single
      cookie (<code>auction_session</code>) so the site remembers you are signed in
      on that device. It is essential to bidding, lasts up to 14 days, and is not
      used for tracking. We use no analytics, advertising or tracking cookies of any
      kind.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Technical logs</strong> — our host, Cloudflare, records standard
      technical data for every visit (IP address, browser, timestamps) to operate
      and secure the site.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Fonts</strong> — the site loads typefaces from Google Fonts, which
      shares your IP address with Google to deliver them.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use it</h2>
    <p>We use this information only to run the auction:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>to verify your email and confirm your identity as a bidder;</li>
      <li>to accept your bids and maintain the running order;</li>
      <li>to email you your verification code, and to tell you if you have been outbid or have won;</li>
      <li>if you win, to contact you to issue an invoice and arrange payment and delivery of the painting.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not use your details for marketing, and we do not sell or rent them.</p>

    <h2>Legal basis</h2>
    <p>
      We process your information to take steps you have asked for and to perform
      the contract of sale if you win (UK GDPR Article 6(1)(b)), and to keep the
      auction secure (our legitimate interests).
    </p>

    <h2>Who we share it with</h2>
    <p>Your information is only shared with the services that run the auction:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosts the site and the database your details are stored in;</li>
      <li><strong>Resend</strong> — our email provider, which processes your email address to deliver the auction emails described above;</li>
      <li><strong>Google</strong> — serves the fonts, as described above.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Each handles your data only on our instructions. We may also disclose
      information where the law requires it. If you win, your details are used to
      complete the sale and may be shared with a courier to deliver the painting.
    </p>

    <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
    <p>
      If you register but do not win, your details are deleted once the auction has
      concluded. If you win, we keep your details for as long as needed to complete
      the sale and to meet our legal and accounting obligations, after which they
      are deleted.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under UK data protection law you can ask us for a copy of the information we
      hold about you, to correct or delete it, or to restrict or object to how we
      use it. To do any of these, email
      <a href="mailto:auction@davesharp.art">auction@davesharp.art</a>. If you are
      unhappy with our response you can complain to the Information Commissioner&rsquo;s
      Office at <a href="https://ico.org.uk">ico.org.uk</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. The current version is always
      the one published here, with the date shown above.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy or your information:
      <a href="mailto:auction@davesharp.art">auction@davesharp.art</a>.
    </p>

    <a class="back" href="/">&larr; Back to the auction</a>
  </main>

  <footer class="foot">
    <span class="foot-links">
      <a href="/terms">Terms &amp; conditions</a>
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy policy</a>
    </span>
    <span>&copy; {year} Dave Sharp &middot; <a href="mailto:auction@davesharp.art">auction@davesharp.art</a></span>
  </footer>
</Layout>
